Did you ever think you would live long enough to get within 124 miles of Mercury? I know I didn't. But thanks to this MESSENGER Mission, The historic flyby netted 500 megabytes of data (now safely downloaded to Earth) and more than 1200 photos covering nearly six million square miles of previously unseen terrain.
